animal.description: Bennett has adorable little freckles on his nose! Around 3 months old, this cutie is a Pit Bull Terrier mix. He is currently being treated for an injured foot but should be back to running around and playing in no time! Bennett came in without a mom or dad so we aren't sure his breed mix or how big he will get but currently we expect Bennett to be medium to large when grown. Bennett's favorite activity is cuddling with his foster family. He wins over everyone he meets, including the kitty in his foster home. They love to play together. Bennett is looking for a family that understands the time, patience, and energy needed to raise a young pup. We require all puppy adopters to provide training that includes: house training, basic training, leash training, and socialization. Additionally, this cutie is going to need proper exercise, mental stimulation, and your attention and love to grow up to be the best companion. We do not allow our dogs or puppies to sleep or live outside; they must be incorporated into your family and be made a priority in your life. In return, you will have the most loving and loyal family member you could ask for. If you think you are ready to add to your family by adopting a puppy, then fill out an adoption application on our website today! We recommend completing the application process and connecting with a adoption coach before looking for a dog or puppy you'd like to adopt. If you're already approved to adopt or if you've adopted from Labs and More before, connect with your adoption coach for the next steps. Your interest in adopting a rescued dog or puppy from Labs and More Rescue is appreciated! Please find our adoption information at www.labsandmore.org. Your adoption donation provides funding for Labs and More, a nonprofit organization which is supported solely by Volunteers and funded by donations. Good news is your adoption donation can be considered tax deductible. So much care is provided to your new dog prior to the adoption, including: spay and neuter, microchip, veterinarian visit(s), vaccinations, and other medical care as needed. Many of the dogs we rescue require extensive surgeries and care prior to adoption. Please understand we are unable to predict future behavior or medical needs of your adopted dog. We provide no guarantees regarding behavior, breed, or age of the dogs. Thank you for rescuing.Thank you for looking to Adopt a Labrador Retriever or other Mixed Breed Dog from California Labradors Retrievers and More Rescue. Please take a moment and go to www.labsandmore.org and click on Adopt to complete our online dog adoption application. If you have any questions email us at doginfo@labsandmore.org or call us at 858-273-5386. Thank you for looking to a rescue group to fulfill your dream of adding a new dog to your life! Dogs + Love = Family

animal.description: Hi, I'm Duke and I'm roughly 8 years old. I am an older fellow, but I have lots of love left to give. Unfortunately, my owner passed away and I didn't have anyone that I could stay with so that's how I ended up with these humans. I have been around other dogs, cats and do well with kids. I am not a fan of crates, so I will need to be in a home where I am allowed to roam the house as I please. I do well in my kennel as far as being potty trained and not chewing things up, so I promise I will be good in my new home. I am a larger guy, weighing a little over 90 pounds, but do mind well on the leash. I would do well placed in a more quiet home as a lot of activity can spook me. I am scheduled to be neutered and am up to date on vaccines and prevention.
animal.name: Duke

animal.description:
This cutie is named Saul! He's happy to cuddle the day away with his trusted people! Saul is quite timid and therefore would do best in a quiet home with a confident dog to show him the ropes and no children in the home. Saul will need socialization and training to allow him to be brave in this world of new noises and experiences. He's only 2 months old and needs to stay close to the Des Moines metro to finish vetting. His adoption fee is $250. Apply at www.foreverhomedogs.org to meet Saul!All adoptions are $200 per dog which include spay/neuter, micro-chipped and up-to-date on required shots. 

Senior dogs, at our discretion, are adopted out at $100 per dog because we know they will have less time with your family and may eventually have more needs as they get older. But we feel these dogs deserve to live out the rest of their lives as part of a loving family.

animal.description:
If you're looking for a canine love bug, look no further. Eva is a pretty 4-year-old friendly pooch that is generous with her heart and wet kisses. Dog lovers know how loyal their four-footed friends can be and when you open your home to a rescue, their gratitude can be off the charts. Won't you consider a meet-and-greet with Eva? This sweet girl may want to be the only pet. Adoption questionnaires are processed in the order in which they're received. All of our dogs and puppies go home spayed/neutered, microchipped, heartworm tested (if at least 7 months old), and up to date on age-appropriate vaccinations. We do our best to update information on adoptable pets as frequently as we can. If you're interested in a specific pet, we recommend that you call the shelter and ask if he or she still is available.
For current adoption fees, please see our website, www.dearbornanimals.org. Adoption fee includes: age-appropriate vaccinations, spay or neuter, microchip, ID tag, fecal / worming, basic physical and behavior assessment. Dogs (6 months and older) receive an occult heartworm test. For an additional $20, cats (12 weeks and older) can be tested for FIV (feline immunodeficiency virus) / FLV (feline leukemia).

animal.description:
Meet Zeke! Located in Bellingham and ready to meet you!

Zeke is a gorgeous mixed breed, approx 1.5 year old, approx 68 lbs. We cannot be sure of his breed since he is a rescue, but we think he looks like a border collie mixed with staffordshire terrier/pit bull, possibly. He has a medium length coat, longer than pit bull hair. He has the most adorable features!!
Zeke is fully vetted and the vet says he looks to be in excellent shape! He is a vibrant boy, joyful and playful. 
 

Zeke absolutely LOVES treats, so he is going to be very trainable! He stands or sits at attention if he thinks you have a treat. This makes training so much easier. He learns new routines and instructions quickly. He is potty trained and crate trained! He cries the first 5 min in crate but then settles. He's getting better and better.

Zeke does love to play with other dogs but needs to be matched with dogs close to his size because he gets excited and May be too rough with little ones. Perhaps matching him with a female would be best, or as a single dog with plenty of exercise with his human would be fine too. 

No cats please!

Zeke absolutely loves people and loves attention. He will make someone an awesome companion and adventure partner! He does great on leash going for walks. 
He loves puzzles and games and learning new things. 
 

The adoption fee is $500. He/she is up to date on vaccines according to age, has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer if needed. This pet is microchipped, spayed/neutered, comes with 6 months of Heartworm preventative, and one month free trial of pet insurance if registered by adopter with insurance company. All animals receive a health certificate (stating that a licensed veterinarian saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, but is not a promise of perfect health.)

Please inquire by submitting an application to alayna@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

Application link: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/19753/generic

Please go to our website to see more about our rescue and what we do! We are very proud of our hard work in saving as many animals as we can, giving them what they need, and matching them with the right families.

$350 for dogs 3-5yrs, and $300 for 6yrs and older


Cornelius is a 75lbs, 4 yr old Mastiff mix.

Cornelius was surrendered to the shelter on 12/9. His owner had died. He was afraid and it took some work from the volunteers to get him out of his kennel into the yard. The volunteers continually worked with him and he kept improving. Unfortunately, he was set to be put to sleep the week of 1/18. The Stanislaus volunteers came together and CalPaws agreed to take Cornelius in. When we assessed him, we could see he was fearful at first but then warmed up to the people around him. He is curious about other dogs but is fearful at first. Were working with a trainer to get a full assessment. Right now, hes decompressing at a home away from the resident dogs. We took him to a local pet store, where there were no other dogs and he did well with strangers as long as they did not approach him too fast or from behind.

The perfect home for Cornelius would be a family with older teenage kids who have had dogs before. Cornelius needs to have a large yard for him to do his zoomies and get his energy out. Right now we would have him as an only dog but if a family has their heart set on him and they have another dog, we will have our trainer assess the situation for compatibility.

Probably best with no cats either.


If you are interested in adopting this dog, please review our adoption process and then fill out an online adoption form at https://www.calpaws.org/adopting. Experience with obedience training is definitely required. We are a small rescue and do not have the resources to respond to inquiries. If a dog is our website, it is still available. We can not arrange meet & greet without an application.

We are always in need of fosters for the amount of dogs we have coming in. Being a foster is such a rewarding experience. If you are interested please review https://www.calpaws.org/fostering

animal.description:
*We are not hosting adoption events at Petco for the public at this time*
We are currently very busy and have over 100 applications to review and on file. Thank you for your patience! We are working to find everyone a companion. 

Chino is a friendly 1 year old Staffordshire terrier mix. 

Chino is a very loving, and friendly boy. He gets along great with people, and other dogs! He loves to go on walks, and adventures! He is all around a wonderful buddy, and companion to have!! He is house and crate trained. 

If you are interested in adopting the first step is to fill out an adoption application on our website aaanimalrescue.org. We are currently very busy! Please reach out to allaboardanimalrescue@gmail.com if you have an approved application on file! Please fill out an adoption application on our website if you are ready to adopt! 

Thank you for your patience and understanding during this difficult time! We are on a mission to find everyone companions, we will continue to rescue dogs weekly! We update our page every Monday evening. We are not currently hosting any Petco adoption events for the public. We will be hosting meet/greet adoption appointments!


Breed and size disclosure: As a rescue all of our dogs come to us from high-kill shelters or other rescues, so we do not get a lot of background or information on these dogs. We occasionally receive the mother with the puppies, but in most cases both parents are unknown. Because of this we do not know the full breeding of the dogs. We are required to list the dogs based on the breeds provided to us on their records, but they are all mixed breeds as far as we know, and we cannot guarantee the actual breeds of any of these dogs. Since the full breeding of the dogs is unknown we can also only give you an educated guess on the full-grown size of the dogs. All of the current information we have on the dogs is listed in their bio above. More information may be available at our adoption event, since a lot of the fosters turn in report cards on how the dog has done in their care when they drop them off. 

Adoption Process: If you are interested in adopting from us, the first step of our adoption process is to fill out an application online at http://aaanimalrescue.org/adoption_app.html. It takes us 24-48 hours to process your application and get back to you, via email. Applications turned in Friday afternoon or Saturday morning will not be processed since we are preparing for or at our adoption event. We do have applications on site at our events, but are not always able to approve them at that time and many of the dogs will already have holds on them, so we suggest you fill out an application prior to attending an adoption event. We can place a hold on one dog per approved applicant after a deposit fee has been received, please do not ask to hold a dog if you have not turned in an application and been approved, for the first hour of our adoption event, so that they can get the first chance to meet and hopefully adopt that dog. After the first hour of the event all dogs are available on a first come, first serve basis. If you already have an approved application on file, there will just be more paperwork and the adoption fee at the event, but you will be able to take home the dog/puppy that day. Since we are foster based and do not have a location, our dogs are only available to meet at our events, unless otherwise noted.

animal.description: Hi! We're Bo and Sadie. We are both 7 year old, pure bred, Catahoula Leopard Dogs. We first met the volunteers at Friends for Life approximately 4 years ago, when our human found herself homeless. We were quickly adopted (thankfully together) by a wonderful family with a large yard and we were very loved. Our family was recently forced to downsize to an apartment and we weren't doing well in that setting. We are a very bonded pair who have been together our entire lives, and we would love to find a home where we can remain together. We're both house trained and know some commands such as sit and down. If you are our happily ever after, we would be thrilled to meet you!All animals are altered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, licensed (dogs). Cats tested for FELV/FIV. Dogs tested for Heartworm. All animals are available to the first family that is a good match, and if we have more than one animal who is a good match, there will be a lottery for all matches. Note that families must have come in to our adoption center and spoken with an adoption counselor prior to any lottery (when we have lotteries, they usually occur on Saturday mornings).

animal.description: Meet Jo, our squishy, wrinkly, snuggly, wobbly, wiggly Sharmadillo. She's part Shar-Pei, you guess the rest, but judging from her butt, we can't help but wonder if an armadillo may have crossed her DNA path along the way. This girl is a 54lb lap dog who loves all creatures she comes in contact with. She fosters with multiple dogs and cats, but she hasn't been formally introduced to the cats, so we can't guarantee a pass. She is housetrained, well mannered, highly social and enjoys sun bathing, short excursions around the neighborhood and as many pats as she can get. Jo wasn't in the best of shape when she arrived in our care, but she has made tremendous progress in a few short weeks and continues to improve day by day. Jo needs to lose ~5-7lbs to be at her ideal weight and we are working towards that goal with light but increased exercise every day. She will be scheduled for a dental by end of February and we anticipate she will be ready for her forever home by then.

animal.description:
This little guy is Jocco, he is a small Terrier mix around 5 yrs old. This low rider was in need if rescue when his family decided they no longer wanted him sadly. But sometimes we think this benefits the dog more then anything, see in his first home there were some younger kids who constantly teased him and poked at him daily, and once he decided to not tolerate it anymore he needed to be gone. So now we feel he would do best in a home with NO KIDS or just in an adult home so he can finally live in peace with no threats anymore. Jocco would you best to be the only pet too. He has now been completely vetted and will be coming to WI now and is hoping to find a real forever home, a home to experience love and happy times. If interested in this cutie an online application can be found at SandiPaws.org
Thank you for your interest in a Sandi Paws Rescue, Inc. Please visit our site at sandipaws.org for more information on our organization or to fill out an application to adopt one of our pets. You can find information for volunteering o. our site as well.

animal.description:
Please welcome Kahlua back to SPR.... she is searching for her furrever home after coming back to the rescue at not fault of her own. Her previous home just didn't have the time for her that she needed. Now that she's in a foster home she is starting to open up and show how much of a sweetie she truly is. 
Kahlua is just shy of 4 years old and we believe she is a Retriever Mix with her beautiful red/brown, soft, medium length coat and black lips. 
She has not had any accidents in the house, does great in her crate, good with both cats and dogs and does well with the older children in her foster home. This snuggle bug is a low key gal who loves to play in the snow and cuddle up with her family. If she sounds like the missing piece in your home, fill out an application today!

animal.description:
Buster is a bit shy at first, but once he gets to know you he will give lots of love and attention! He is approximately 1-2 years old and weighs around 40 pounds. He is potty trained and knows the commands sit and stay, and loves to play fetch. He would do well in a home with older children and as an only pet.If you have any questions or would like to meet this pet, please email contact@stlpetrescue.com. Information about the rescue and adoption process can also be found at stlpetrescue.com along with a full listing of our adoptable pets. 

Our adoption fees:

Cats range from $110 to $150 

Dogs range from $250 to $350

This fee includes: felv/fiv/heartworm testing, worming, flea and ear mite treatments, age appropriate vaccinations, spay/neuter, rabies vaccination, lab work, dental or other medical surgical treatments as deemed necessary by our team of veterinarians and a microchip with free registration.

The adoption process includes an interview, application, adoption contract, which includes a return obligation if adopter is needing to rehome pet. The adoption process may include a home visit.

St. Louis Pet Rescue adopts to the St. Louis Metropolitan area.

animal.description:
RCHS does not conduct DNA tests on dogs who enter our facility therefore we are unable to guarantee breed or breed mix. Information provided by shelter staff, volunteers, and veterinarians is used to give a best estimate as to a dog's breed make up. We do our best to inform adopters about the potential breeds for each dog.

We are a dog only facility so we do not know how most of our dogs will be with cats. Even if a dog is surrendered to us and said to be good with cats there is no way to be sure the dog will be good with your cats. We do have a 7 day foster-to-adopt program so that you can see how the dog interacts with your cats before adoption.

animal.description:
Tucker is a senior fella seeking a home of his own. He would prefer to shine as the only dog in the household.

The Adoption Process


	If you are ready to meet the pet, please fill out an online adoption application by copying and pasting the following link into your internet browser: https://www.petstablished.com/adoption_form/10666/generic
	Once your application is submitted, we will contact the vet reference provided. If you do not yet have a vet, please provide three personal references these could be family and friends who can attest to your pet parenting skills.
	A volunteer will schedule a phone interview with you. The interview and application help our fosters find their forever home by ensuring a good match. 
	The Louisa Humane Society does not have a brick and mortar facility, so all of our pets are in foster care. Once approved, the foster parent will reach out to arrange a visit. The foster family can tell you all about her likes, dislikes, and little quirks. 
	The application and visit do not oblige you to adopt, but if youre ready to take the pet home as your furry forever friend, the adoption fee is $150.

animal.description:
Yuki is a Japanese word that can mean both snow and happiness. Our little Aussie mix puppy looks like a joyful little snowball. Playful yet independent, he likes to be around people but will entertain himself, going off to explore on his own. Its always fun wrestling with his brother or chewing on toys. He has a quiet personality and enjoys being cuddled.

Yuki is hearing and vision impaired so hes learning touch commands. Because he is food motivated, the learning part is fun. He has a blast running through a toy tunnel and frolickiing in a ball pit. Yuki would love a home with a fenced-in yard, ideally with another dog to play with and a family that is home most of the time to take him on great adventures.Yuki is up to date on vaccinations, neutered, microchipped, and current on heartworm/flea and tick prevention. Also included in his adoption is a Fi GPS collar and one year of GPS service subscription. If he were to escape, as soon as he leaves the safe zone you set around your home, you are alertedso that you can find Yuki's whereabouts. Youll also be able to see how many steps per day he takes to ensure he gets the right amount of exercise, alongside many other features to explore in the Fi mobile app.

animal.description:
If you have ANY QUESTIONS or are truly interested in adopting any animal from PAW Animal Shelter Please, fillout an adoption application FIRST! WE are a high intake No Kill Shelter ran by a staff of 4 and do not always have time to answer every question asked by so many. If you are a good fit for the animal you are interested in -we will call to speak with you, If we feel you are not a good fit , we will contact you about other pets that may be a good fit for your home. Many people are losing the opportunity to adopt the animal they want because they fail to put in an application and the pet was adopted before we could answer your email. .If you have applied for an animal in our facility and have not received a response within 7 days, PLEASE call or contact us again. Though we do our best in trying to answer all emails in a timely manner, sometimes things get away from us, get lost or misplaced. It is never our intention to ignore a request about an adoptable animal in our facility.

Sandy Brown, Director, PAW Animal Shelter

Harley is a 3 year old dachshund/miniature pinscher mix. He weighs 18ish pounds. Harley was very much loved, but the owner was selfless in surrendering so he can live his best life. He is settling in and I don't think his tail has stopped wagging yet. He gives kisses, loves kids, gets along with other dogs, and loves to play outside! Harley does great on a leash. A fenced yard is not a must have, but because he has lots of energy a fence would be best. He likes other dogs, but is used to be an only dog, so either are fine with him. His only downfall is that he needs to work on his potty training. He just needs the time to get it down!

animal.description:
1220122

I am heartworm positive. Heartworm is NOT contagious. The rescue covers the cost of treatment at the rescue's vet. 
I am part pittie, so I need a single family home. I can NOT go to a home in a city or county with pittie restrictions. 

I'm as pretty as a flower and as sweet as a bowl of ice cream! I am about 55-65 pounds, 2 yr old grey pitty and my coat has the most beautiful markings. I am the best family gal in the world. I love kids, love to cuddle on the couch or chair with my family. I ended up in a shelter in Texas. I was not happy there at all... Thats when the nice people at DCCR rescued me! One of my favorite things to do is snuggle up close to you and roll around to get belly rubs. I havent been around cats much so unsure there. I am friendly and love most other dogs though! I am a great listener and will follow you from room to room, or just take a nap if your moving around to much. I love to feel part of a family and want to protect you.

On a leash I can pull and bark at other dogs until I get comfortable with you! Then Im totally fine no pulling, as I love going on walks. I have never had an accident in the house and will go to the door when I need to go out. If you are not paying attention and I really need to go, I will paw at you. I love car rides, soft surfaces, watching TV, windows and squirells and couches. When my foster parent leaves, I get a little anxious in a kennel and do not love to be in one, so they leave me out in the house and I am just fine. When you get home I talk to you and tell you how much I missed you, and show you my toothy grin, dance around and tell you how much I missed you! Cutest thing ever. All around I am the greatest dog ever is what my foster family says. Seriously my foster dad says that I am the sweetest dog best dog ever and they wish they could keep me but they are keeping my daughter!

Are you my new forever family? I would love a home, with a fenced in yard and I guarantee many kisses in exchange for belly rubs!

Sinead OCollar is a big sweetheart! She is a Cattle Dog so she does herd other people & pets. She loves to do zoomies and would love a home with a yard where she can have a daily outlet for her energy. Sinead loves nothing more to be around her humans and can be protective of her people, so she will need slow intros to other dogs who approach before she is comfortable. We would not recommend dog parks, daycare, or similiar environments. Sinead hopes to find a quieter, single-family suburban home. She loves being on the dock near the water and would be a great lake dog!

Sinead would do best with older kids and teens as she can be anxious around the energy of younger children and will pace. She is crate trained with no barking unless she hears a loud noise and does not have accidents in her crate. Sinead is looking for an adopter who will continue working on her leash skills as she can pull a bit in excitement. She is considered a flight risk as she is curious and has gotten out of fenced areas when off leash.

Sinead is a wonderful girl who will make a great addition to her furever family!

animal.description: Say hello to Ashtor (or Ash for short)! This sweet boy is ready to be at your side as your #1 pal in life. He's very curious and likes to keep tabs on what his humans are up to, and when the opportune moment arises, he'll make sure to nuzzle his head right into your lap for some pets. He may appear a bit on the shy side at first, but if you go slow with him and show him kindness, you will easily gain his trust. Ashtor is a very chill, low maintenance dog who is content being lazy around the house while you work - making him the perfect companion for anyone working from home. He can handle being home alone too, with or without a crate, and has shown to be a quick learner when it comes to figuring out the right place to go potty. He's just as happy to be your buddy for daily walks, despite being a lower energy pup in the house. Once the leash goes on and he gets out the door, he gets so excited to explore the world with you - and it just makes him all the more ready for snuggling downtime later! Sweet Ashtor is just waiting to find his perfect match. Come meet him to see if that could be you!

animal.description: Riley has a beautiful face complemented with her adorable Shar Pei snout. She loves hard and plays hard and snorts and grunts when she's all riled up. She loves to run as fast as she can around the coffee table and then stop abruptly, which is your cue to start chasing her! Riley loves meeting people and is so excited to see them. She is the biggest cuddlebug EVER and likes to be the little spoon when on the couch or in bed. She will always make herself as small as possible to fit however you're sitting or laying. She has a lot of playful energy and her favorite game is chase, and she's also a big fan of rubber toys and bones. She loves going for walks and would be thrilled to have a backyard to romp around in. Riley is fully house-trained and does well in crate, even if she fusses for a brief moment. She also does well free to roam the house as long as all trash/food are put up. She knows the her basic commands, such as sit, down, stay and off. She's a strong girl, but she walks well on leash with a gentle leader. She also knows when it's bed time and always is the first one in bed. Riley has lived with a 4 year-old lab and did just fine, and she could go home with a well-matched doggie sibling. She's also done well with children of all ages. This quirky and affectionate lady is going to make some family very happy. Come meet her!

animal.description: Justin Theroux is a beautiful black and white pit bull. He's subservient to cats, but also fiercely loyal to his people. He needs a slower introduction to strangers because he wants to make sure his people are protected. He's been muzzle trained and understands commands like 'sit, 'place, 'lay down, and 'come. He loves his toys, and will steal them from other people and dogs. One of his cutest behaviors is when he takes toys out of his toy box. He also doesn't bark much and when he does, it is typically limited to barking at deer. Justin gets along with some dogs, but needs a well matched pup friend. His best friend is a female German Shepherd who is very chill. He will have a reaction if he is frightened by someone, even if he's been friendly with them before so he needs a patient home who can be understanding with his quirks. What Justin needs next in his development is someone that can put together a routine and stick to it. Come meet this loyal pup, he's waiting for his dedicated forever home.

animal.description: Wombat is a skip-the-salad-and-if-you're-going-to-McDonald's-get-me-a-large-fry kinda guy. Meaning he knows what's good and nothing sounds better to him than snacking on the couch or sleeping in your lap! That's not to say he doesn't love his walks, though he prefers to mosey along and sniff the flowers on a loose leash. He's a low energy lover, excited to play with a tennis ball for a few minutes before laying back down at your feet, ready for the shower of belly rubs and snuggles you can't help but give this adorable boy. He enjoys his quiet time and is more than happy to spend his afternoon basking in the sun or napping by your desk chair. And if you catch a glimpse of those soulful eyes staring at you, you'll see all the appreciation and love he has reflecting right back. Wombat has had his history of defensive behavior such as food guarding or getting uncomfortable with strangers who get into his space without warning so he would do best in a low traffic home with adults or a family with older children. He is an extremely intelligent boy who learns quickly and has his own set of tricks such as 'Sit,' 'Down,' 'High Five,' 'Wait,' 'Lay Down,' 'Let's Go,' and most recently learned 'Stay' and 'Come' after only a few tries! He quickly trusts those who take the time to get to know him and will double the amount of affection he's given in return, so long as that affection is given with his consent. And as a bonus, he has gotten along well with dogs he has met and his foster's two resident cats! His chill attitude and calm demeanor make him a perfect match for any low-key home with other chilled out pets. For an individual or family looking to adopt a sweet, smart, and peaceful pup, look no further! If you're not convinced by that cute face, let him sway you with all the love he has to give!

animal.description:
Aries is a handsome and active Border Collie who is looking for a new home. He was recently surrendered to a shelter after 9 years with his family when they could no longer care for him due to circumstance.

Aries is about 40 pounds, and age hasn't slowed him one bit! He loves to run and fetch, playing well along with his canine buddies. He is currently in foster care and has done well with dogs big and small, and cats too. Aries has herding breed behaviors including being nippy, and he will guard his bed from his foster siblings. His current foster has a large outdoor space, but Aries does not roam, he prefers to stay close, and likes to be in the house with his people. He is becoming more affectionate day by day, and is very treat and ball motivated. He will need a home with folks with breed experience.

animal.description:
Nope, it’s not Baby Yoda, but close enough... Prancer is here and ready to break the internet!  

Prancer is another in our quirky chihuahua collection and looking for a specific home... this 2 year old bigger chi (13 lbs) was owned by an elderly woman who never socialized him and as a result is a very nervous guy who takes time to trust.  When his foster mom rescued him he was terrified, untouchable, and severely overweight, but he’s now a healthy weight and has gained a lot of confidence.  Once he loves you, you are his whole world ? and he will be a loyal devoted protector to his chosen person. He fears and hates men and wants to be the only guy in your life, and is looking for a home with preferably just one woman.   It probably won’t be love at first sight at least on his part, and he need some patience to earn his trust in order to see his sweet side underneath the “tough guy” attitude he invokes when scared.   It’s hard to tell from the photos but he has a gorgeous unique spotted red merle coat... and of course those giant expressive eyes ?, and so much personality.  

Prancer is currently in foster with other animals but gets jealous sharing attention and would be best as your one and only ? Valentine ?   If you are happily single and looking for a devoted dedicated best friend and sidekick, please email njwoof@cs.com for an appointment to meet Prancer!

Due to COVID-19, we will not be holding our Sunday adoption events until further notice, but we can schedule socially distant appointments with a specific dog outdoors at our vet’s office:
VCA Morris Plains Animal Hospital 
3009 Rt 10 East 
Morris Plains (Denville on GPS) NJ 07950
Now is the perfect time to open your home to a needy dog!  Submit an application from our website www.secondchance.petfinder.com to speed up the adoption process
All our dogs reside in foster care in Northern NJ until adoption. We are a small all-volunteer organization focused on rescuing local dogs from area shelters, as well as accepting some surrenders and puppy mill rescues.

animal.description:
BACON was one of four we took as former strays  at age 10 months.  Siblings looked like Brittney Spaniel and Beagle mixes.  She favors the Beagle gene. 

She weighs about 30 pounds. 

She is somewhat of an alpha girl with females who are submissive.  We want her to go into a home with a male or as the only dog.  Currently with a larger female who is a strong gal and there are no conflicts with her, but when I added a submissive female her size (actually her sister so it could have been sibling rivalry stuff that went on) BACON bullied her.  

Because she did that and is a strong girl, we will not put her in a home with small kids, but kids over age 10 would and should be a very good fit.  

She can be pretty playful, another reason for older kids. 

BEAUTIFUL gal who wants an active family.  She is curious, playful with the dogs, always excited to see me. Has not been a jumper, and so too I think she would be pretty smart and easier to train. She likes treats. 

Call Marilyn at 573-722-3035 to adopt from 9:30am to 9:30pm Central Time. 

DO CALL or DO DO DO leave a phone number if you send an email message. 

Adoption fee is $250.

animal.description: Louie is a 2 year old genrle and shy yorkie. He needs sponsorship for his medical care to help him get ready for eventual adoption.  He came to us with a dislocated femur.  Louie needed surgery which was done in early January.  He is on cage rest and limited  movement for 9 weeks which is the estimated healing time. We are guessing he will need 6 months of care and sponsorship before we can place him for adoption.  If you would like to help with his care, we would be grateful.  You can donated to him via:  PayPal.Me/RescueTails or via Zelle at RescueTailsAnimalWelfare@gmail.com.  Our website has donation links as well: RescueTailsAnimalWelfare.org  Thank yoU!

animal.description:
Meet POKER FACE, a little girl who speaks her mind and will be a candidate for separation anxiety if babied.  She is looking for a family who can teach her independence.  Prefer a home with another dog or cats to keep her company.  

OH SO CUTE!   This gal has a square frame, legs are normal length, not short. Fur is so soft and airy.  Muzzle is slightly underbite, little bit of a smashed nose. Big round eyes, and may I say in again, she is sooooooooooo cute ... 

Should mature in the 35 to 45 pound range.  

The mother to this litter is a Lab and Heeler looking dog who weighs 46 pounds. Fathers were probably the Brindle 30 male and a 35 pound Airedale looking male, who was surely from the Shih Tzu looking mother. There were 14 dogs on this property we helped rescue. Sizes from less than 20 pounds to 46 pounds.

$300 to adopt. We pay for the spay or neuter, and one more puppy shot as well as rabies shot if puppy vetting done with one of our partner vets in our area who are:

. Animal Health Center of Dexter MO
. Bollinger County Veterinary Service in Marble Hill MO.
. Helping Hands Veterinary Clinic in Advance MO
. Lacroix Pet Hospital in Cape Girardeau MO
. Tilsit Road Animal Clinic in rural Jackson MO

Otherwise if you use your vet we give a $50 refund with proof of spay or neuter when of age.

First shot and microchip applied for all pups was at 7.5 weeks of age. They were isolated and protected, regularly dewormed, and regularly given Marquis to control tummy issues in such a large pack. Second shot weekend of 1/29/21. They leave us with a puppy kit: De-wormer, Marquis, and one application of Advantage Multi.

House and hand raised.

Call 573-722-3035 between 9:30am to 9:30pm Central Time to adopt . IF you send a reply here INCLUDE YOUR PHONE NUMBER. I call people before I email them back.

PHONE NUMBER PLEASE

animal.description:
Meet FLASHY RUMMY.    

INTENCE color coat for this little male we call RUMMY, my very favorite card game!

White on all four feet, little underbite, little bit of smash look to the face, and a fun loving little dude!  Thick shorter legs... When you look at this litter he stands out.

Really good temperament. A little independent and curious. Playful too. 

Weighed 9 lbs and 4 ounces at 9.5 wks of age.  Should mature around 35 to 40 pounds.  

The mother to this litter is a Lab and Heeler looking dog who weighs 46 pounds. Fathers were probably the Brindle 30 male and a 35 pound Airedale looking male, who was surely from the Shih Tzu looking mother. There were 14 dogs on this property we helped rescue. Sizes from less than 20 pounds to 46 pounds.

$300 to adopt. We pay for the spay or neuter, and one more puppy shot as well as rabies shot if puppy vetting done with one of our partner vets in our area who are:

. Animal Health Center of Dexter MO
. Bollinger County Veterinary Service in Marble Hill MO.
. Helping Hands Veterinary Clinic in Advance MO
. Lacroix Pet Hospital in Cape Girardeau MO
. Tilsit Road Animal Clinic in rural Jackson MO

Otherwise if you use your vet we give a $50 refund with proof of spay or neuter when of age.

First shot and microchip applied for all pups was at 7.5 weeks of age. They were isolated and protected, regularly dewormed, and regularly given Marquis to control tummy issues in such a large pack. Second shot weekend of 1/29/21. They leave us with a puppy kit: De-wormer, Marquis, and one application of Advantage Multi.

House and hand raised.

Call 573-722-3035 between 9:30am to 9:30pm Central Time to adopt . IF you send a reply here INCLUDE YOUR PHONE NUMBER. I call people before I email them back.

PHONE NUMBER PLEASE

animal.description:
LADYBUG ~ spayed Boxer mix, 5 years old, 53 lbs

I know you don't think I look like a Ladybug but once you get to know me, you'll understand that I am super sweet and the name fits me perfectly.  I love your attention, I literally crave it!  I am good with all different dogs and all different people.  I walk well on a leash and I am told I am a "Well mannered and well behaved gorgeous girl".  Sound pretty great to you?

If you are interested in meeting me, please contact us at DOGS@SAVINGPAWS.COM to set up an appointment.  All of our dogs are in foster homes so you will need to schedule an appointment to come meet the dog/puppy. We require approved applications to adopt an animal through Saving Paws Animal Rescue, Inc., so please serious inquiries only. We are a volunteer run animal rescue so please allow us time to get back to you for an appointment. Our applications can be found on our website at www.savingpaws.com 

Adoption fees include; Spay/Neuter, Micro-chipped, age appropriate vaccines including distemper, bordatella and if old enough rabies vaccines, dewormed, heartworm tested(if old enough)

We are always in need of foster homes, so if you are interested in opening your home and heart to an animal in need until they find their furever homes, please  email dogs@savingpaws.com.
Saving Paws Animal Rescue Inc. is a no-kill animal welfare nonprofit organization dedicated to saving homeless, abandoned and special needs pets. Please consider making a donation on our Web site, www.savingpaws.com - every donation, no matter how small, helps us save lives.

Cooper (GA) is a male Poodle mix rescued from a Georgia kill shelter at 12 years old in November 2020. Cooper is good with people of all ages and other dogs. After some TLC at our vet partners, Cooper is doing well for an older boy. He has a bronchial condition and may have a permanent cough, as well as dry eye, requiring daily meds for both conditions for life, he also requires a special diet. Cooper
is a very loving boy and just wants to be by his people. He's a little shadow dog. He's amazing on the leash and does well meeting pups around the neighborhood. He still loves to run after his little stuffed toys. He is generally very quiet and rarely barks. Cooper
needs a happy home filled with love where he will be a cherished member of his forever family for all his senior years. If you can open your heart to Cooper and give him a leaf on your family tree, please apply online to adopt Cooper (GA) at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.

NO LONGER ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS DUE TO THE OVERWHELMING AMOUNT OF INTEREST SHE HAS RECEIVED.

Animal Profile: Black Jack is a cute lab mix that will be joining us from Texas soon! She is estimated to be 1 year old and currently weighs 40 pounds. She is dog and cat friendly! We will post more info as we get to know her.

Seattle Foster Update:
BlackJack

is doing great! She's been one of the easiest snuggliest dogs we've had at our house (out of fosters, dog-sitting, or our own). She's a quick study, calm, and gentle when playing or taking treats. We have left her a couple times in the crate during the day when we went out and she did fine, but in general, she has been stuck to my side like glue. She's adjusted to our wake schedule within the week and hasn't chewed on anything she's not supposed to. (She has carried my shoe to me once, to let me know she needed to go out - but no damage to the shoe!). She's had no accidents since the first day and has found her spot to go in the yard with regularity & quickness. She'll need some help with leash training but she is eager to please and pays good attention to me when we are out on a walk, so I think it will come easily with practice. I have seen 2 instances where she's a bit wary of tall men, so she will need more training and confidence building to overcome that fear.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued from euthanasia at a high-kill shelter in Texas and is joining us via our TX rescue partner to find a forever home. This dog will be available for adoption in Seattle once evaluated in a foster home.

About Foster to Adopt Program:
Fosters provide a safe landing spot for dogs transitioning from the shelter environment and help prepare the dogs for adoption. You provide the love and structure, and we take care of everything else! We cover all vet care, and drive the adoption process. Average length of foster is 2-3 weeks. Fosters do get first consideration for adoption, if desired.

Apply to foster online at www.doggoneseattle.org/foster-application

Three runts in this litter and this one is the alpha!

Meet JACK OF HEARTS at 7 lbs at 9.5 wks. of age he should mature around 25 pounds or so.  He should mature about 28-30 pounds at maturity. 

VERY short legs, this little man is a HOOT!

Not a bossy or mean alpha. He mellowed out a lot at age 8 weeks. I guess the litter is so laid back there was no more competition so he felt he could let his fur down and just blend back in. 

Likes being held but is not mushy.  Somewhat independent. 

Red merle, this little guy is a conversation maker with his interesting build and hooty personality.

A mild alpha puppy, he will be a fun and playful dog.  VERY good in his pack and doe not need to play act being an alpha.  

The mother to this litter is a Lab and Heeler looking dog who weighs 46 pounds. Fathers were probably the Brindle 30 male and a 35 pound Airedale looking male, who was surely from the Shih Tzu looking mother. There were 14 dogs on this property we helped rescue. Sizes from less than 20 pounds to 46 pounds.

$300 to adopt. We pay for the spay or neuter, and one more puppy shot as well as rabies shot if puppy vetting done with one of our partner vets in our area who are:

. Bollinger County Veterinary Service in Marble Hill MO.
. Helping Hands Veterinary Clinic in Advance MO
. Lacroix Pet Hospital in Cape Girardeau MO
. Tilsit Road Animal Clinic in rural Jackson MO

Otherwise if you use your vet we give a $50 refund with proof of spay or neuter when of age.

First shot and microchip applied for all pups was at 7.5 weeks of age. They were isolated and protected, regularly dewormed, and regularly given Marquis to control tummy issues in such a large pack. Second shot weekend of 1/29/21. They leave us with a puppy kit: De-wormer, Marquis, and one application of Advantage Multi.

House and hand raised.

Call 573-722-3035 between 9:30am to 9:30pm Central Time to adopt . IF you send a reply here INCLUDE YOUR PHONE NUMBER. I call people before I email them back.

animal.description:
Brax is aprx 1.5 year old male American Staffy who hasn't had the best start. 
Unfortunately, Brax was a victim of some form of abuse that damaged his vocal cords and he has some scar tissue build up on his neck. Have no fear though, it does not prevent him from "Wooing" his happy "woos" or singing you songs in a chihuahua-like pitch. He also likes to "tip tap" when he's excited. And he does get excited - particularly when you call him a handsome good boy! 
Despite being treated poorly by his former "humans" Brax loves all of the things. Cats, other dogs, humans young and old. He is very gentle when he is being a good boy! He enjoys walking on his leash, playing with other dogs, or running around in the yard.
+Brax resource guards his food, snackies, and water. However, there is a solution to this issue & it's an easy one! If you have another dog separate meal areas are needed and treats should not be handed out together. He is a patient boy and will wait his turn for his treats! 


*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
BERTIE loves to hug and cuddle :-) She is the largest of the litter. She's very loving and good-natured. She likes to be with humans and also plays well with dogs. She's good with cats too.  She has a light undercoat that shines beautifully under her thick black coat :-) Super affectionate, very playful.

Her adoption fee includes her spaying, vaccine series, rabies, deworming, microchip. She was born on a reservation we work with Sept 16, 2020.

Do you live in our adopting area? Do you have another young playful friendly male dog of similar adult breed size?  If yes to both questions, then please proceed with the application process below! :-)

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. No young children for our adoptions please. Puppies MUST adopt to families that have another young friendly playful dog of similar breed size when grown. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

$250 to adopt. We pay for the spay or neuter, and one more puppy shot as well as rabies shot if puppy vetting done with one of our partner vets in our area who are:

. Animal Health Center of Dexter MO

. Lacroix Pet Hospital in Cape Girardeau MO
. Tilsit Road Animal Clinic in rural Jackson MO

Otherwise if you use your vet we give a $50 refund with proof of spay or neuter when of age.

First shot and microchip applied for all pups was at 7.5 weeks of age. They were isolated and protected, regularly dewormed, and regularly given Marquis to control tummy issues in such a large pack. House and hand raised.

Hello! Our names are Bullis (male) and Maryland (female). We were tossed away into the cold to starve and a nice lady took us in. Australian Shepherds Furever found us and sent us to our best friend and foster mom Megan Pyatt! Because we were so starved she had to feed us very small meals till we could eat like normal dogs. We are now ready to get the last steps of our vetting done to find our furever family.

We really need to stay together. We are about 8 months old and we have been though so much and are very bonded. We are both very loving and outgoing but will need some training and potty work. Our foster mom has worked hard with us. She says we are good babies.  We just got spayed/neutered and we will be ready shortly to go to our furever homes!

If you're interested in adopting us please fill out the application and see if we are a good fit for you. Thank you!

https://www.australianshepherdsfurever.org/adoption-application

Our mix puppies are $395 each, but we are offering a $100 discount for this bonded pair to keep them together.

All adoption fees are used for future rescue efforts.

Russo is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Russo is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~2 years 
Weight: ~55lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Hasn't been left alone much due to COVID and will need an adopter that can continue to work on this. He does take time to settle when left alone.
Dog sociability: He's selective about his dog friends. On walks, he is often reactive towards dogs his size or larger. Would benefit from continued leash training and an adopter that can continue to work on socialization. 
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown
Ideal home: Russo is looking for a home in a quieter neighborhood where he can practice his leash skills! He is also working on being left solo, so thin walls won't work for this guy. 

Russo is the snuggliest dog and a total sweetheart! He always wants to be with his person and is a great work from home companion. He would love to sit in your lap and go for long adventures in the car. Russo enjoys walks and playing outside in the snow but is a huge fan of naps, too! Russo has been great with new people and wants to share his love with everyone. He is a true foodie and mealtime is the absolute best time of day for Russo! 

Russo's adoption fee is 300. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative.

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

Santos is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Santos is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~5 years 
Weight: ~83lbs (overweight and needs to lose some)
Housebroken: Working on it! He needs to be on a strict schedule. 
Crate trained: Doing well with his crate training and sees the crate as his safe spot in the home.
Dog sociability: Friendly! Santos needs to be adopted into a home with a resident dog as he is his most confident self when he is with a dog companion.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown, but shy/timid so older kids only
Ideal home: Santos is a sweet, sensitive dog looking for a patient home that can allow him time to come out of his shell. He is timid of loud noises and will do best in a quieter neighborhood. He requires a resident dog in his forever home.

Santos will take one look at you and you'll instantly be smitten with his David Bowie eyes! Santos gets an A+ in social distancing, both from strangers and sometimes within the home (he cares about everyone's health!). He'll let you into his inner circle once he's thoroughly assessed you and decided you're safe to hang with. With his pup pals, his interview process is less thorough and he's been known to make friends immediately. Taking naps in a blanket fort or under your desk for hours is a favorite hobby as is showing off his moves once he figures out how to jump onto the couch for more napping activities. Santos is an excellent work from home buddy. He'll make sure you stay on task but won't let you forget to take a walk or pause for a snack (creamy peanut butter, preferred). Santos truly lives up to his name and he is most certainly, a saint. 

Santos' adoption fee is 300. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. Santos has moderate dental calculus and fractured incisors. He will benefit from at-hme dental care and a dental cleaning with potential extractions. He is overweight and would benefit from gradual weight loss.

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
GIZZY is affectionate and playful. She is smart and will do well in doggie daycare and training classes once she's old enough. She loves to cuddle with humans and play with dogs. She's good with cats too. 

Her adoption fee includes her spaying, vaccine series, rabies, deworming, and microchip. She was born on a reservation we work with November 19, 2020.  

** Do you live in our adopting area? ** Do you have another young playful friendly male dog of similar adult breed size? ** IF YES to these questions, then please proceed with the application process below! :-)

We have specific ADOPTION and COVID rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. No young children for our adoptions please. Puppies MUST adopt to families that have another young friendly playful dog of similar breed size when grown. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be able to reply to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

AdoptaGSD.org

Please consider that some of these dogs have been abandoned or ignored by their previous owners, having little interaction with someone who cares about them.

When adopted, they will need time to adjust to the changes in their life.

Hi, my name is Pepper, and I'm a beautiful, all black girl who was surrendered to a shelter when my former owners were forced to move in with family, and as a result, I got to spend my seventh birthday looking through the bars of a kennel. My former family had me since I was a puppy, so as you might guess, my world has been turned upside down. Upon arriving in CO, the volunteers immediately noticed that I had to say hi to every single person I met. I'm now settling into a foster home that I share with two adults and two other dogs and I'm doing great! Many people may pass me by due to my age, but I hope there's a special someone/family out there who would open their home and heart(s) to a sweet girl like me. I'm housetrained, crate trained and I know some basic commands. I do need to lose a few pounds, but I'd be really happy to join you on a daily walk if you would like a buddy! If you are interested, please go to adoptagsd.org and submit an online application. My adoption fee is $200.

animal.description:
Hi my name is Meatball!
I’m an 11 wk old bully pup.  I’m full of energy and very playful.  My favorite place to lay in this cold weather is on top of the heat vent.  Or early morning snuggles on moms lap.  My favorite toys are my chew bones, any ball, toys that squeaks and stuffed animals. Wait ... I like all toys! I also like to snuggle down in my dog bed with a soft blanket.  Potty training is pretty new for me but I will catch on fast. I have mastered sit and lay down . I like to be helpful and get inside the dishwasher every time my foster mom opens it.  I don’t get why she keeps putting me back on the floor.  I’m going to need a forever home that is experienced with my breed and prepared to work with a trainer to be sure I become the best me I can.  I can be pretty stubborn sometimes & need a family to help me work on that.  A home where I’m not left alone much would really be great and a fenced yard too. I’m super cute as you can see & growing real fast . I’m told I’m going to be a big boy some day.  I do have an eye issue and the vet said it should be removed.  It will be done along with my neuter and while this is not ideal I was born this way and it is all I know!

animal.description:
Meet Bandit... we think he is 3 years old, but we're not sure because the circumstances he found himself in may have aged him.  

Bandit has not had an easy life.  

Bandit was owned by someone who should have never been allowed to own pets.  He was kept outside most of life, which explains his unusual coloring for a Husky.  The exposure to direct sunlight made Bandit lose all the pigment in his beautiful coat. 

Bandit, above all, needs TLC.  He needs a life filled with good food, lots of time indoors feeling safe.  He LOVES attention and he LOVES to play! 

He has a prolapsed anus, which we are trying to get fixed.  

Bandit would do well in a home paired with a female dog, but he is good with all including cats and kids. 

Experienced Husky owners as preferred.  

Bandit didn't deserve the hand he was dealt, but we know that with the help of Mayte's Rescue and with the love and care of someone who is willing to open up their heart and home - the rest of Bandit's life can be great.
